  <!-- WHO IS IT FOR / NOT FOR -->
  <section class="pf-section" style="background:#f8fafc;">
    <div class="container">
      <h2 style="text-align:center;">Is a Power Flush Right for Your Formby Property?</h2>
      <p class="pf-sub">We assess every Formby system honestly before recommending a flush.</p>

      <p style="font-weight:700;color:var(--navy);margin-bottom:0.75rem;text-align:center;">Power flushing IS right for you if</p>
      <div class="pf-who-grid" style="margin-top:0;">
        <div class="pf-who-item pf-who-yes"><span class="pf-who-icon">✓</span><div><strong>Your Formby system is more than 5 years old and shows signs of contamination</strong><p>Cold spots, slow warm-up, noisy boiler or uneven zone heating. A power flush resolves these in the majority of cases on Formby sealed systems.</p></div></div>
        <div class="pf-who-item pf-who-yes"><span class="pf-who-icon">✓</span><div><strong>A new boiler was installed on your existing Formby system without a flush</strong><p>If you had a new Worcester Bosch or Vaillant installed 3 to 7 years ago on existing radiators and pipework without a power flush, sludge from the old system may already be inside the new heat exchanger. A power flush now and a written report both clean the system and document maintenance for warranty purposes.</p></div></div>
        <div class="pf-who-item pf-who-yes"><span class="pf-who-icon">✓</span><div><strong>You have a multi-zone Formby system with uneven zone performance</strong><p>If one zone heats faster than another, or if certain radiators consistently underperform within a zone, targeted power flushing of the slower zone and affected radiators resolves this in most cases.</p></div></div>
        <div class="pf-who-item pf-who-yes"><span class="pf-who-icon">✓</span><div><strong>You are installing a new boiler on your existing Formby system</strong><p>All major manufacturers require a clean system as a warranty condition. The written power flush report from us is your evidence before the new boiler is connected. On a large Formby system, this warranty protection is particularly financially significant.</p></div></div>
      </div>

      <p style="font-weight:700;color:var(--navy);margin:1.5rem 0 0.75rem;text-align:center;">Power flushing may NOT be right if</p>
      <div class="pf-who-grid" style="margin-top:0;">
        <div class="pf-who-item pf-who-no"><span class="pf-who-icon">!</span><div><strong>Your boiler keeps losing pressure</strong><p>Pressure loss means a leak, not sludge. Power flushing does not seal leaks. The leak must be identified and repaired first. We assess this before recommending any flush.</p></div></div>
        <div class="pf-who-item pf-who-no"><span class="pf-who-icon">!</span><div><strong>Your underfloor circuit is showing symptoms rather than your radiators</strong><p>Underfloor circuits can have different issues to radiator circuits. If your underfloor is cold but radiators are fine, the underfloor manifold or pump may be the issue rather than system-wide sludge. We assess the specific cause before recommending a full flush.</p></div></div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>


