  <!-- HOW IT WORKS -->
  <section class="pf-section" style="background:#f8fafc;">
    <div class="container">
      <h2 style="text-align:center;">What Happens During a Formby Power Flush</h2>
      <p class="pf-sub">A step-by-step breakdown including how we handle multi-zone Formby systems.</p>
      <div class="pf-steps" style="margin-top:2rem;">
        <div class="pf-step"><div class="pf-step-num">1</div><div><strong>System assessment, 20 to 30 minutes</strong><p>We identify the system configuration, single zone or multi-zone, any underfloor circuits, note zone valve positions and check each zone independently. We test a water sample for magnetite and assess contamination level across the system.</p></div></div>
        <div class="pf-step"><div class="pf-step-num">2</div><div><strong>Cleaning chemical added and system run</strong><p>Professional-strength cleaning chemical introduced. The system is run with zone valves open to all zones, allowing the chemical to circulate through every circuit and begin loosening sludge from all internal surfaces.</p></div></div>
        <div class="pf-step"><div class="pf-step-num">3</div><div><strong>Machine connected. Zone-by-zone flushing begins.</strong><p>Power flush machine connected at the pump head. For multi-zone systems, we flush one zone at a time, zone valves correctly positioned so the machine flow concentrates on one circuit at a time rather than dispersing through all zones simultaneously.</p></div></div>
        <div class="pf-step"><div class="pf-step-num">4</div><div><strong>Individual radiators treated within each zone</strong><p>Within each zone, every radiator is isolated and flushed individually. Heavily contaminated radiators receive additional agitation. Underfloor loops are flushed through the manifold individually where present.</p></div></div>
        <div class="pf-step"><div class="pf-step-num">5</div><div><strong>Neutraliser added. Inhibitor dosed. All zones balanced.</strong><p>Neutraliser added and pH confirmed. System refilled with clean water and full-strength inhibitor dosed to BS 7593 standard. Every radiator balanced in every zone. System pressure set. Full multi-zone heating cycle run to confirm all zones performing correctly.</p></div></div>
        <div class="pf-step"><div class="pf-step-num">6</div><div><strong>Written report issued same day</strong><p>Written report covering date, contamination level found, system configuration, chemicals used, inhibitor dose and final condition. This is your warranty evidence document for Worcester Bosch, Vaillant or any other major manufacturer warranty claim.</p></div></div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>


  <!-- WHY CHOOSE -->
  <section class="pf-section" style="background:#f1f5f9;">
    <div class="container">
      <h2 style="text-align:center;">Why Formby Homeowners Choose Ideal Plumbing for Power Flushing</h2>
      <p class="pf-sub">Fixed price. Multi-zone expertise. Warranty report included. Honest assessment. Our own Gas Safe engineers. All Formby L37 postcodes.</p>
      <div class="pf-why-grid">
