  <!-- LIMITATIONS -->
  <section class="pf-section" style="background:#f8fafc;">
    <div class="container">
      <h2 style="text-align:center;">What Power Flushing Cannot Fix</h2>
      <p class="pf-sub">We give Formby homeowners honest information before every job.</p>
      <div class="pf-limitations" style="margin-top:2rem;">
        <div class="pf-limit"><span class="pf-limit-x">✕</span><div><strong>It will not fix a boiler that keeps losing pressure</strong><p>Pressure loss means a leak in the circuit. Power flushing does not seal leaks. The leak must be identified and repaired before a flush is appropriate.</p></div></div>
        <div class="pf-limit"><span class="pf-limit-x">✕</span><div><strong>It will not fix a zone valve that has failed mechanically</strong><p>A seized or failed zone valve needs replacing. We can identify and replace faulty zone valves on the same visit as the flush where required.</p></div></div>
        <div class="pf-limit"><span class="pf-limit-x">✕</span><div><strong>It will not fix a failing underfloor manifold pump</strong><p>If the underfloor circuit is cold because the manifold pump has failed, the pump needs replacing. Power flushing cleans the water circuit but does not fix mechanical component failures.</p></div></div>
        <div class="pf-limit"><span class="pf-limit-x">✕</span><div><strong>It is not a permanent solution</strong><p>Sludge and magnetite will build up again over time. Annual inhibitor checks and a magnetic filter slow the process. We recommend a power flush every 5 to 7 years on a well-maintained Formby system.</p></div></div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>


