      <p class="pf-sub">Straight answers to what Formby homeowners ask most before booking.</p>
      <div class="pf-faq">
        <details class="pf-faq-item"><summary><span class="pf-faq-tag pf-tag-orange">COST</span>&nbsp; How much does power flushing cost in Formby?</summary><div class="pf-faq-body"><p>A power flush in Formby costs £350 for up to 10 radiators and £450 for 11 to 15 radiators. Both prices include all cleaning chemicals, full inhibitor dose to BS 7593 and a written system report. For larger properties with 16 or more radiators or with underfloor circuits in addition to radiators, call us for a fixed price tailored to your system.</p></div></details>
        <details class="pf-faq-item"><summary><span class="pf-faq-tag pf-tag-navy">WARRANTY</span>&nbsp; Does a power flush protect my Worcester Bosch or Vaillant warranty?</summary><div class="pf-faq-body"><p>Yes. Worcester Bosch and Vaillant both require a clean system as a warranty condition and specify that a clean system should be confirmed and documented when the boiler is installed and maintained. A written power flush report from a Gas Safe registered engineer is your evidence that the requirement was met. Without this evidence, the manufacturer can reject a warranty claim on the grounds of system contamination. We issue the written report on the same day as the flush.</p></div></details>
        <details class="pf-faq-item"><summary><span class="pf-faq-tag pf-tag-orange">ZONES</span>&nbsp; Can you power flush a multi-zone system in my Formby house?</summary><div class="pf-faq-body"><p>Yes. Multi-zone systems must be flushed zone by zone with zone valves correctly positioned for each zone in turn. We flush one zone at a time, machine flow concentrated on one circuit while the others are isolated. This delivers a complete flush for each zone rather than a diluted partial flush across all zones simultaneously. Underfloor circuits are flushed through the manifold separately. We have extensive experience with multi-zone Formby systems.</p></div></details>
        <details class="pf-faq-item"><summary><span class="pf-faq-tag pf-tag-navy">NEW BOILER</span>&nbsp; My new boiler was installed without a power flush. Is it too late?</summary><div class="pf-faq-body"><p>No. A power flush now, after the new boiler was installed, will clean the existing system and protect the heat exchanger from continued sludge damage. The written report documents the maintenance for warranty purposes. For a Worcester Bosch or Vaillant with 5 to 7 years of warranty remaining on a large Formby system, a power flush now is very worthwhile from a warranty protection perspective.</p></div></details>
        <details class="pf-faq-item"><summary><span class="pf-faq-tag pf-tag-green">GAS SAFE</span>&nbsp; Are you Gas Safe registered for Formby power flushing?</summary><div class="pf-faq-body"><p>Yes. All power flushing in Formby is carried out by our own directly employed Gas Safe registered engineers. Verify at <a href="https://www.gassaferegister.co.uk" target="_blank" rel="noopener">gassaferegister.co.uk</a>. We never use sub-contractors.</p></div></details>
